[{"id":40195,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>The initial current in the coil will be,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>V</mi><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>20</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>.</p><p>Average e.m.f. developed in the coil will be,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#949;</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>&#981;</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>L</mi><mi>i</mi></mrow><mi>t</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>20</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>100</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>400</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40192,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>M</mi></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>M</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mi>M</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>M</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/cd0f0ba9-33d5-4c16-821c-892cef71d0ca-image.png\" style=\"width: 230px; height: 101px;\" /></p><p>Here self inductances are in series&nbsp;but their mutual inductances are linked oppositely.</p><p>As the inductors connected are in series opposition, hence magnetic flux will be opposing each other. Therefore,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>M</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40157,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Horizontal component of earth's magnetic field, </p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">H</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup><mo> </mo><mi>Wb</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>.</p><p>Induced <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>emf</mtext><mo> </mo><mi>e</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>B</mi><mi>H</mi></msub><mi>v</mi><mi>ℓ</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup><mo>×</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>5</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (29 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40183,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>B</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#969;</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mi>B</mi><msup><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#969;</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>B</mi><msup><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#969;</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>B</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>L</mi><mi>&#969;</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a0a133cd-b1e3-492f-b6ce-24ba9f603a69-9893978_1.PNG\" style=\"width: 202px; height: 112px;\" /></p><p>Linear velocity at the distance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;from the centre can be written as,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>x</mi></math>.</p><p>Therefore, induced EMF due to small element will be,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mi>&#949;</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>B</mi><mi>v</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>B</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p><p>Integrating both sides, we get</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8747;</mo><mi>d</mi><mi>&#949;</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>&#8747;</mo><mi>B</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#949;</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>B</mi><mi>&#969;</mi><msubsup><mo>&#8747;</mo><mn>0</mn><mi>L</mi></msubsup><mi>x</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>B</mi><mi>&#969;</mi><msup><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (24 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40211,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#949;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>L</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>I</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><msubsup><mo>&#8747;</mo><mn>0</mn><mn>4</mn></msubsup><mi>t</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msubsup><mo>&#8747;</mo><mn>0</mn><mn>1</mn></msubsup><mi>d</mi><mi>I</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>I</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>L</mi><msup><mi>I</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mfenced><mn>12</mn></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>144</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9e9c7fdb-a169-41cf-a71e-74c40eb9c382-image.png\" style=\"width: 173px; height: 174px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40138,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["\\(\\varphi=\\mathrm{AB}, \\varepsilon=0\\)","\\(\\varphi=0, \\varepsilon=0\\)","\\(\\varphi=0, \\varepsilon=\\mathrm{NAB} \\omega\\)","\\(\\varphi=\\mathrm{AB}, \\varepsilon=\\mathrm{NAB} \\omega\\)"],"answer":2,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/tRqC4OVurqIDgEyxkTpQjnBLQepjWGwUa6_bu56ua_M.original.fullsize.png\"><br>\n\n$\\begin{aligned}\n\\phi & =\\mathrm{BAN} \\cdot \\cos (\\omega \\mathrm{t}) \\\\\n\\varepsilon & =\\frac{-\\mathrm{d} \\phi}{\\mathrm{dt}}=\\mathrm{BA} \\omega \\mathrm{~N} \\cdot \\sin (\\omega \\mathrm{t})\n\\end{aligned}$\n\nWhen $B$ is parallel to plane, $\\underline{\\underline{\\omega t}}=\\frac{\\pi}{2}$\n$\\Rightarrow \\phi=0, \\varepsilon=\\mathrm{BA} \\omega \\mathrm{~N}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (29 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40212,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>Iv</mi><mi>&#8467;</mi></mrow><mi>Rr</mi></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>&#960;</mi></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>Iv</mi><mi>&#8467;</mi></mrow><mi>Rr</mi></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><mi>&#960;</mi></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>Iv</mi><mi>&#8467;</mi></mrow><mi>Rr</mi></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>Iv</mi><mi>&#8467;</mi></mrow><mi>Rr</mi></mfrac></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>The induced current in the wire&nbsp; will be due to the motional EMF developed in the moving resistor&nbsp; and that back emf developed&nbsp; at that point will be&nbsp; equal to&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mi>B</mi><mi>L</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo></math>velocity of the conductor</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo></math>perpendicular magnetic field</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mo>=</mo></math>length of conductor</p><p>We know magnetic field due to a long wire is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>Hence the induced current&nbsp;across wire will be :</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>I</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>e</mi><mi>R</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>I</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>Iv</mi><mi>&#8467;</mi></mrow><mi>Rr</mi></mfrac></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (05 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40199,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>The EMF&nbsp;is induced in the coil when it is moving&nbsp;in a uniform magnetic field,<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>e</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>B</mi><mi>v</mi><mi>l</mi></math>&nbsp;and the current,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>e</mi><mi>R</mi></mfrac></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>B</mi><mi>l</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>002</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>002</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>R</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>002</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (01 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40169,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5d6c8bc7-7667-4b17-8b7e-ef248b88dcf4-image.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 193px;\" /></p><p>From the graph, it can be seen that the value of the magnetic field at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mT</mi></math>, whereas the magnetic field at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mT</mi></math>.</p><p>The formula to calculate the magnitude of the induced emf is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><msub><mi>&#949;</mi><mtext>ind&#160;</mtext></msub></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>&#981;</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mi>d</mi><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mi>B</mi><mi>A</mi></mrow></mfenced></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mi>A</mi><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>B</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>B</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;is the slope of the given graph.</p><p>Hence, the value of the induced emf can be calculated as follows:</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnspacing=\"0px\" columnalign=\"right center left\"><mtr><mtd><msub><mi>&#949;</mi><mtext>ind&#160;</mtext></msub></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mT</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mT</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd/><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>8</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mV</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (11 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40223,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["<math><mn>0.103</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>","<math><mn>0.002</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>","<math><mn>0.324</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>","<math><mn>0.016</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>The instantaneous current in an LR circuit is given by the equation :<br />(instantaneous current)&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mi>s</mi></msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow><mi>L</mi></mfrac></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></msub><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi></math>&nbsp;are the instantaneous current, saturation current, resistance, time and inductance respectively.</p><p>Given that the current becomes so percent of saturation current.<br /><math><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>0.8</mn></mrow></mfenced><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow></msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mrow><mi>e</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mtext>&#937;</mtext><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mtext>&#937;</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mtext>&#937;</mtext></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>0.8</mn><mo>=</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>0.8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>100</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi></math><br />Therefore, the time is:<br /><math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi>l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow><mo>&#8289;</mo><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0.8</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mrow></mrow><mrow><mn>100</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">ln</mi></mrow><mo>&#8289;</mo><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mrow></mrow><mrow><mn>100</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0.016</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40140,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["$0.5024 \\mathrm{~V}$","$\\mathrm{~V}$","$0.2512 \\mathrm{~V}$","$0.1256 \\mathrm{~V}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{B}=0.4 \\mathrm{~T} \\\\ & \\mathrm{r}=20 \\mathrm{~cm} \\\\ & \\omega=10 \\pi \\mathrm{rad} / \\mathrm{s} \\\\ & \\mathrm{E}=\\frac{1}{2} \\mathrm{~B} \\omega \\mathrm{R}^2 \\\\ & =0.2512 \\mathrm{~V}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (28 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40159,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>The formula to calculate the change in the magnetic flux associated with the given loop can be written as</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mo>∆</mo><mi>ϕ</mi></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>-</mo><mi>B</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>cos</mi><mi>θ</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>-</mo><mi>B</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>l</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi>cos</mi><mi>θ</mi><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p>The formula to calculate the induced emf is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mi>ε</mi></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>∆</mo><mi>ϕ</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>∆</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mi>B</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>l</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi>cos</mi><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>∆</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p>From equation (2), it follows that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mi>ε</mi></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mi>cos</mi><mn>60</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (27 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40246,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/KJltPs9gN6K3jYlhzaaC4cM9xM0UIYF2VG0Akp-Ia1A.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/eelhiZD6J_B3XLGKWEgkgdCnEqkGUw-VPN34kpon0QQ.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/BBARl0UeNSk4Ld5O9OF6LqjsHw9aewCS0pz0rWZ-Agc.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/uFLWjrrRnuF7lfhp4sqmfBedSLYHCZE9oHP5_iF1Nis.original.fullsize.png\"><br>"],"answer":3,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (19 May Online)","image":null},{"id":40249,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["development of air current when the plate is placed.","induction of electrical charge on the plate","shielding of magnetic lines of force as aluminium is a paramagnetic material.","electromagnetic induction in the aluminium plate giving rise to electromagnetic damping."],"answer":3,"solution":"Oscillating coil produces time variable magnetic field. It cause eddy current in the aluminium plate which causes anti-torque on the coil, due to which is stops.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (Offline)","image":null},{"id":40215,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>tan</mi><mn>45</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msubsup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>100</mn></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>50</mn><msqrt><mn>2