ction","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The force on the rod is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>i</mi><mi>l</mi><mi>B</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>F</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>B</mi><mi>v</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>l</mi><mi>B</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>F</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>B</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>l</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>v</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>i</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p><p>The data given is</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#937;</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mi>l</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace></math></p><p>Substituting the values in equation (i)</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>18</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (10 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40259,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["$0.05 \\mathrm{~s}$","$0.1 \\mathrm{~s}$","$0.15 \\mathrm{~s}$","$0.3 \\mathrm{~s}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"$\\mathrm{I}=\\mathrm{I}_{\\circ}\\left(1-\\mathrm{e}^{-\\frac{\\mathrm{R}}{\\mathrm{L}}\\mathrm{t}}\\right)$\n$0.693=\\frac{\\mathrm{R}}{\\mathrm{L}} \\mathrm{t}$\n$\\mathrm{t}=\\frac{.3 \\times 0.693}{2}=0.1 \\mathrm{sec}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2005","image":null},{"id":40234,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["$\\frac{\\mu_0 \\mathrm{I}}{2 \\mathrm{R}} \\omega \\mathrm{r}^2 \\sin \\omega \\mathrm{t}$","$\\frac{\\mu_0 I}{4 R} \\omega \\pi r^2 \\sin \\omega t$","$\\frac{\\mu_0 I}{2 R} \\omega \\pi r^2 \\sin \\omega t$","$\\frac{\\mu_0 \\mathrm{I}}{4 \\mathrm{R}} \\omega \\mathrm{r}^2 \\sin \\omega \\mathrm{t}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"According to Faraday's law of electromagnetic induction,\n$$\n\\begin{array}{r}\ne=-\\frac{d \\phi}{d t} \\text { and } \\phi=B A \\cos \\omega t=B \\pi r^2 \\cos \\omega t \\\\\n\\Rightarrow \\quad e=-\\frac{d}{d t}\\left(\\pi r^2 B \\cos \\omega t\\right)=\\pi r^2 B \\sin \\omega t(\\omega) \\\\\n\\therefore e=\\frac{\\mu_0 I}{2 R} \\pi \\omega r^2 \\sin \\omega t\\left(\\because B=\\frac{\\mu_0 I}{2 R}\\right)\n\\end{array}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr Shift 2 Online)","image":null},{"id":40268,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["$(\\mathrm{It})^{1 / 2}$","IT","I/t","$\\mathrm{I}^{2} \\mathrm{t}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"From Faradays law of electrolysis, $\\mathrm{m} \\propto$ it.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2002","image":null},{"id":40190,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msup><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msup><mi>l</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msup><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msup><mi>l</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<blockquote><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/db54367e-5890-4534-988f-c7bfec6a66dc-image.png\" style=\"width: 382px; height: 200px;\" /></p><p>Let a current,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>I</mi></math> pass through the square loop of side,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math>. The magnetic field at the centre <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>O</mi></math>,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>Magnetic</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>field</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>due</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>to</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>each</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>side</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#8901;</mo><mfrac><mi>I</mi><mrow><mi>L</mi><mo>/</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mn>45</mn><mo>&#8728;</mo></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mn>45</mn><mo>&#8728;</mo></msup></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>I</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>I</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p></blockquote><blockquote><p>Magnetic flux linked with the small square loop,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#981;</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>B</mi><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>B</mi><msup><mi>l</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>I</mi><msup><mi>l</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>Mutual inductance of the coil,&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>&#981;</mi><mi>I</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msup><mi>l</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40247,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["Statement 1 is true, Statement 2 is false.","Statement 1 is true, Statement 2 is true, Statement 2 is the correct explanation of Statement 1.","Statement 1 is false, Statement 2 is true.","Statement 1 is true, Statement 2 is true, Statement 2 is not the correct explanation of Statement 1."],"answer":1,"solution":"Self inductance of a long solenoid is given by\n$$\nL=\\frac{\\mu_0 N^2 A}{l}\n$$\nMagnetic field at the centre of solenoid\n$$\nB=\\frac{\\mu_0 N I}{l}\n$$\nSo both the statements are correct and statement 2 is correct explanation of statement 1","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (19 May Online)","image":null},{"id":40228,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["$\\frac{n_{1}}{n_{2}}$","$\\frac{n_{2}}{n_{1}} \\cdot \\frac{r_{1}}{r_{2}}$","$\\frac{n_{2}}{n_{1}} \\cdot \\frac{r_{2}^{2}}{r_{1}^{2}}$","$\\frac{n_{2}}{n_{1}}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"The rate of mutual inductance is given by\r\n\r\n$$\r\n\r\n\\mathrm{M}=\\mu_{0} \\mathrm{n}, \\mathrm{n}_{2} \\pi \\mathrm{r}_{1}^{2} \\quad \\ldots(\\mathrm{i})\r\n\r\n$$\r\n\r\nThe rate of self inductance is given by\r\n\r\n$\\mathrm{L}=\\mu_{0} \\mathrm{n}_{1}^{2} \\pi \\mathrm{r}_{1}^{2} \\quad \\ldots(\\mathrm{ii})$\r\n\r\nDividing (i) by (ii) $\\Rightarrow \\frac{\\mathrm{M}}{\\mathrm{L}}=\\frac{\\mathrm{n}_{2}}{\\mathrm{n}_{1}}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (11 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40209,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msubsup><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mi>a</mi></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mi>a</mi></mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>d</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mi>a</mi></mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>d</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mi>net</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mi>net</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mi>a</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/55f82c0f-1c3f-4ab9-b9b9-33c181686cb6-image.png\" style=\"width: 236px; height: 186px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (16 Mar Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40126,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["197","80","100","280"],"answer":0,"solution":"EMF induced $\\varepsilon = A \\dfrac{dB}{dt} = A\\mu_0 n \\dfrac{di}{dt}$<br>$\\varepsilon = A\\mu_0 n \\, i_0 \\omega \\cos\\omega t$<br>current induced $i = \\dfrac{\\varepsilon}{R} = \\dfrac{\\pi r^2 \\mu_0 n i_0 \\omega}{R} \\cos\\omega t$<br>So $i = \\dfrac{\\pi r^2 \\mu_0 n i_0 \\omega}{\\sqrt{2} R}$<br>$= \\dfrac{\\pi \\times 10^{-4} \\times 4\\pi \\times 10^{-7} \\times 500 \\times 10 \\times 10^3}{\\sqrt{2} \\times 10}$<br>$= \\dfrac{20\\pi^2}{\\sqrt{2}} \\times 10^{-6}$<br>$\\simeq \\dfrac{197}{\\sqrt{2}} \\, \\mu A$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (23 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40242,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["$\\frac{m^2}{A}$","$\\frac{m^3}{A s}$","$\\frac{m^2}{A s}$","$\\frac{A s}{m^3}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"According to question\n$\\mathrm{E}_{\\mathrm{y}} \\propto \\mathrm{J}_{\\mathrm{x}} \\mathrm{B}_{\\mathrm{Z}}$\n$\\therefore$ Constant of proportionality\n$\\mathrm{K}=\\frac{\\mathrm{E}_{\\mathrm{y}}}{\\mathrm{B}_{\\mathrm{Z}} \\mathrm{J}_{\\mathrm{x}}}=\\frac{\\mathrm{C}}{\\mathrm{J}_{\\mathrm{x}}}=\\frac{\\mathrm{m}^3}{\\mathrm{As}}$\n$\\left[\\right.$ As $\\frac{E}{B}=C$ (speed of light) and $\\left.J=\\frac{I}{\\text { Area }}\\right]$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (25 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":40131,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"$E = B\\omega A \\sin\\omega t$<br>$15.4 \\times 10^{-3} = \\dfrac{1}{2} \\times 100 \\times \\dfrac{22}{7} r^2 \\times \\dfrac{1}{2}$<br>$r = \\sqrt{\\dfrac{15.4 \\times 28 \\times 10^{-5}}{22}}$<br>$R = 14 \\text{ mm}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (22 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40146,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"Case-I:\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/40ICr09IOfMfea6ofQ8WIVFtA51c8p0h2VXGoKZWvG8.original.fullsize.png\"><br />$i=\\frac{20}{R} \\Rightarrow R=4 \\Omega$\nCase-II:<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/aYHJcavg8RiqhaKYu2Ea7SeQVrTZ5q8hqb7-fDs1Rac.original.fullsize.png\"><br />$\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{i}=\\frac{20}{\\mathrm{Z}} \\\\ & 4=\\frac{20}{\\sqrt{\\mathrm{R}^2+\\mathrm{X}_{\\mathrm{L}}^2}} \\Rightarrow \\sqrt{\\mathrm{R}^2+\\mathrm{X}_{\\mathrm{L}}^2}=5 \\\\ & \\mathrm{R}^2+\\mathrm{X}_{\\mathrm{L}}^2=25 \\Rightarrow \\mathrm{X}_{\\mathrm{L}}=3 \\Omega \\\\ & \\mathrm{L}=\\frac{3}{2 \\pi \\mathrm{f}}=\\frac{1}{2 \\times 50}=\\frac{1000}{100} \\mathrm{mH} \\\\ & \\mathrm{L}=10 \\mathrm{mH}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (09 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40256,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["N.A.B. $\\omega$","N.A.B.R. $\\omega$","N.A.B","N.A.B.R"],"answer":0,"solution":"NBA $\\omega$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2006","image":null},{"id":40197,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Induction","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Given,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1000</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo></math>and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>07</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math></p><p>The maximum emf generated is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>&#949;</mi><mi>max</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>N</mi><mi>B</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>&#969;</mi></math>,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>N</mi><mi>B</mi><mi>A</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>f</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1000</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>07</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>140</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></math></p><p>Thus, maximum emf is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>439</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>&#8776;</mo><mn>440</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (24 Jun Shift 2)","image":null}]